      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Critics label substantive due process as \"judicial activism\" because they believe judges are overstepping their authority by creating new rights rather than strictly following the text of the Constitution. They argue that this approach undermines the democratic process by allowing unelected judges to override the will of the people and their elected representatives. This tension highlights a fundamental debate about whether the Supreme Court should act as a neutral interpreter of the law or as an active participant in shaping societal values.",
      "source": "target",
