      "content": "That makes sense. To help them understand the stakes, could you elaborate a bit more on that \"neutral interpreter\" side? Like, if a judge refuses to use substantive due process because they are being a \"neutral interpreter,\" what actually happens to the rights of marginalized groups in that scenario? I want to show if being \"neutral\" can sometimes result in outcomes that feel pretty unjust.",
